	- Magnetization in colisionless plasma
		- Colisionless plasma: Period between collisions >> Cylotron period.
		- Calc: Magnetization vector of collisionless plasma
		- Calc: Magnetization current of collisionless plasma
		- Calc: Charge density associated with magnetization currents (continuity equation).
		- Remmember: Magnetic susceptibility in magnetic materials (relação entre M e H).
		- Note: Our relation between M and B is non-linear.
		- Note: Plasma cannot be considered as magnetic material...
	- Uniform Electromagnetic Field
		- Equation of motion (component by component)
		- Decoupling of equations of motion: Inhomogeneous harmonic oscillator.
		- Solution to the equation of motion (vx, vy, vz)
		- Position of particle (x, y, z).
		- Note: Termo de velocidade dependente apenas dos campos E e B.
		- Def: Drift velocity.
	- Uniform Electromagnetic Field: Vector equations
		- Equation of motion (vector form).
		- Separação: Velocidade parapela e perpendicular. 
		- Separação: Campo E paralelo e perpendicular.
		- Separação: Velocidade perendicular dependente de velocidade perpendicular em outro frame + ve
		- Equações de movimento da parte paralela
		- Equações de movimento da parte perpendicular
			- Usando Identidade: Ep = -Ep x B x B / B^2.
			- Calc: Equação de movimento da parte perpendicular
			- Calc: Equação de movimento da parte perpendicular no outro referencial
		- Note: Definir the drift velocity such as term zero out to reduce problem to uniform B-Field.
		- Def: Drift Velocity.
		- Note: Identical situation for uniform B-Field in this other frame
		- Calc: Passagem para frame normal. Drift velcity.
		- Calc: Vetor de frequencia cyclotron.
		- Calc: Solução geral vetorial (velocidade).
		- Note: There is a drift velocity.
	- Drift due to external uniform force
		- Equation of motion
		- Calc: The same process as before: Separation into parallel/perpendicular
		- Calc: Drift velocity of external uniform force.
		- Calc: Drift velocity due to gravity acceleration field g.
		- Calc: Current density due to drift velocity caused by gravity field.
		- Calc: Current density due to drift velocity caused by external force.
		- Example: Earth Ionosphere. 
			- Data: B-Field: 0.5e-4 tesla. Altitude: 300Km. electron density = ion density = 10^12 / m^3-
			- Note: Earth B-Field is almost perpendicular to g-Field. Approximate to perpendicular. =).
			- Calc: Drift velocity of electron in Earth's ionosphere due to gravity.
			- Calc: Drift velocity of positive oxygen ion in Earth's ionosphere due to gravity.
			- Calc: The net gravitational current density in ionosphere.
			- Calc: The net gravitational current in the overall Earth's ionosphere.
			- Note: The direction of the current.
