Termos da Particula carregada em campo magnético não-uniforme
	- Perturbação de campo uniforme
		- Remember: Gyroradius.
		- Variation of magnetic field over larmur radius is too low (delta B << B)
		- Tracking the motion of the guiding center
	- Spatial Variation of Magnetic Field
		- Dyad of B-Variation. Note: 9 components.
		- 8 independent components: B-Field has no divergence
		- No current condition
			- Scalar Magnetic Potential
			- Laplace equation for scalar magnetic potential
		- Show: Divergence terms (terms of the divergence)
		- Show: Gradient terms (dBz/d)
		- Show: Curvature terms (d/dz)
		- Show: Shear terms
	- Divergence Terms
		- Assume: B-Field in origin has only component z.
		- Def: Magnetic Field lines.
		- Equation of the magnetic field lines.
		- Differential equation: ds x B = 0.
		- Condition of the dx, dy, dz of the magnetic field lines.
		- Calc: B-Fields in x,y direction. (Taylor expansion).
		- Calc: dx/dz and dy/dz of the magnetic field lines.
		- Note: Magnetic field lines diverges or converges
		- Draw: Magnetic field with divergence terms only.
	- Gradient Term
		- Gradient in x-direction term.
		- Draw: B-Field lines with gradient in x-direction.
		- Equation of B with gradient in x-direction.
		- Calc: Current of B-Field with gradient in x-direction.
		- Note: Same consideration for y-direction.
	- Curvature Term
		- Curvature in x-direction term.
		- Draw: B-Field lines with curvature in x-direction.
		- Equation of B with curvature in x-direction.
		- Calc: Current of B-Field with curvature in x-direction.
		- Note: Current is opposite to one of gradient form
		- Note: Same consideration for y-direction.
	- Gradient, curvature and divergence term
		- B-Field with curvature and gradient in x-direction having no current.
		- Draw: B-Field lines with gradient and curvature in x-direction.
		- Draw: B-Field lines with gradient, curvature and divergence term. (A 3D Draw)
	- Shear Terms
		- Shear terms.
		- Draw: B-Field with shear.
	- Equation of motion first-order approximated
		- Assumption: Magnetic field in origin has only z-component
		- Approximation: Difference of B-Fields is too low in one gyroradius.
		- Taylor expansion of the magnetic field
		- Equation of motion
	- Coordenadas cilindricas
		- Escrita de B em cilindrico e cartesiano. Relaçao entre componentes Bx, Br, etc.
		- Escrita das derivadas parciais
		- Calc: Divergence terms.
		- Calc: Gradient terms.
		- Calc: Curvature terms.
